    "18We have now shown thatF = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i, R ▷, R ◁, R ⊊, R + }, RO(S, ⊑)⟩ is a full possibility frame.The following lemma is the motivation for defining R ⊊ and R + as above.",
    "Informally, it says that we can write a formula that takes us from a regular open O to the canonical encodingσ O -of the shrunken O -⊊ O. Lemma 2.48.",
    "Let α:= ♢ + ⊤∧□ + (□ ◁ p∧¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p).",
    "For any model M based on F, if p M ∩ RO(R) = ↓O, then α M = ↓σ O -.Proof.",
    "Note that M, x ⊩ ♢ + ⊤ iff x is a set σ of pairs."
